import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, f_regression

# Load the data
data = pd.read_csv('SUPSI.csv')  # Sostituisci '/path/to/' con il percorso corretto del file

# Display the first few rows of the data
print(data.head())

# Check for missing values
missing_values = data.isnull().sum()

# Get descriptive statistics
descriptive_stats = data.describe()

print(missing_values)
print(descriptive_stats)

# Calculate and display the correlation matrix
correlation_matrix = data.corr()
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))
sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', fmt=".2f", linewidths=0.5)
plt.title('Correlation Matrix')
plt.show()

# Perform univariate feature selection
feature_columns = data.columns.drop(['RealLat', 'RealLon'])
target_columns = ['RealLat', 'RealLon']
selector = SelectKBest(score_func=f_regression, k='all')
selected_features = []
for target in target_columns:
    selector.fit(data[feature_columns], data[target])
    selected_features.append(feature_columns[selector.get_support()])
selected_features = list(set(selected_features[0]).union(set(selected_features[1])))

print("Selected features:", selected_features)

# Scatter plots for RealLat vs selected features
fig, axs = plt.subplots(len(selected_features), figsize=(5, 40))
for i, feature in enumerate(selected_features):
    axs[i].scatter(data[feature], data['RealLat'], alpha=0.2)
    axs[i].set_title(f'RealLat vs {feature}')
    axs[i].set_xlabel(feature)
    axs[i].set_ylabel('RealLat')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Scatter plots for RealLon vs selected features
fig, axs = plt.subplots(len(selected_features), figsize=(5, 40))
for i, feature in enumerate(selected_features):
    axs[i].scatter(data[feature], data['RealLon'], alpha=0.2)
    axs[i].set_title(f'RealLon vs {feature}')
    axs[i].set_xlabel(feature)
    axs[i].set_ylabel('RealLon')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
